ed categories. Testable at Unit with user fixture (limited browsing history) and comprehensive product fixture (10+ categories). Diversification logic is deterministic algorithm execution on in-process data.","test_description":"Create user with browsing history limited to 2 categories (e.g., 'shoes', 'clothing'). Create product fixture with 8+ diverse categories (including unbrowsed ones like 'electronics', 'home', 'sports'). Run recommendation engine. Assert at least one result is from a category not in user's browsing history.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.65,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"New users with no history receive popularity-based recommendations instead of empty results","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Tests fallback path in ranking algorithm. Real failure: returns empty set for new user, or tries to filter on non-existent history causing error. Testable at Unit with new user fixture (empty purchase/browsing history) and popularity-ranked product fixtures.","test_description":"Create a new user with purchase_history=[] and browsing_history=[]. Create product fixtures with popularity scores. Run recommendation engine for this user. Assert result is non-empty and contains products with highest popularity scores.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Click tracking records correct product ID, position, and timestamp for each interaction","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: A Unit test mocking the tracking backend always passes even if persistence layer loses data, corrupts fields, or has timestamp bugs. Real failure requires verifying data actually persists in storage. Integration test with real/test database catches: field mapping errors, null values, timestamp precision loss, missing records.","test_description":"Generate recommendations for a user. Simulate clicks on 2 products at specific positions (e.g., position 0 and position 4). Query tracking database. Assert each logged entry contains: correct product_id, correct position, valid timestamp within 5 second tolerance of click time. Verify exactly 2 records exist for this user.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"Response time stays under 200ms for a catalog of 100,000 products","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"REAL-INFRA + SCALE: Unit test on 100 products would pass while production with 100k products times out. Real failure (slowness) only observable at scale. Cannot mock data count. Requires Integration test with actual test database containing 100k realistic products with full indexes.","test_description":"Populate test database with 100,000 products with realistic distributions: categories (20 categories), price ranges, popularity scores, stock status. Measure wall-clock time to generate recommendations for a test user. Assert response completes in ≤200ms. Run 10 times to account for variance.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.3,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"Purchased products are deprioritized in subsequent recommendations","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Tests algorithm's weighting of purchase history. Real failure: algorithm doesn't check purchase_history or doesn't reduce score for purchased items. Testable at Unit: run algorithm with user fixture, simulate purchase (update fixture), run again, verify ranking changed. If purchase history requires database queries, Integration might be needed for robustness.","test_description":"Create user with initial recommendations including product P1. Note P1's initial rank position. Mark product P1 as purchased in user's purchase_history. Run recommendation engine again for same user. Assert P1 is either absent or ranked significantly lower (e.g., moved from position 2 to position 15+) than in first run.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.55,"Integration":0.4,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":10,"description":"Recommendation results are deterministic—same request returns identical ranked list","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Pure algorithm determinism test. Real failure: algorithm produces different rankings for same input (e.g., uses hash iteration, random seed varies, uncontrolled floating-point rounding). Testable at Unit: call algorithm twice on identical user/product state, compare results. No I/O or external state.","test_description":"Create a user fixture with fixed purchase_history, browsing_history, and preferences. Generate recommendations twice with no intervening user activity or data changes. Assert both responses have products in identical order (verify product_id sequence is byte-identical across runs).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13603,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13603},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"db36ed3d-ed06-454a-a84c-232d2bb4614e","uuid":"a1fef26b-94df-4dd8-a109-cfac40d50d19"}
